.TH "gfs2_setattr_size" 9 "gfs2_setattr_size" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gfs2_setattr_size \- make a file a given size
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gfs2_setattr_size
.BI "(struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "u64 newsize "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "inode" 12
the inode
.IP "newsize" 12
the size to make the file
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The file size can grow, shrink, or stay the same size. This
is called holding i_rwsem and an exclusive glock on the inode
in question.
.SH "RETURN"
errno
